Name: acute salpingitis
Definition: A spastic cerebral palsy that affects all four limbs. The individuals have difficulty with walking and talking.

Name: chronic salpingitis
Definition: A chronic salpingitis that is caused by is nodular thickening of the narrow part of the uterine tube

Name: pyosalpinx
Definition: A chronic salpingitis that is caused by is nodular thickening of the narrow part of the uterine tube
